## Getting started

```sh
go mod tidy
{{if .Has "air"}}make dev          # run with hot reload (Air)
{{else}}go run ./cmd/api
{{end}}```

The server listens on `:8080` by default. Override it with the `ADDR`
environment variable.

A health check is available at `GET /healthz`.
{{if .Has "godotenv"}}
## Configuration

Copy `.env.example` to `.env` and adjust the values. They are loaded at startup
via [godotenv](https://github.com/joho/godotenv).
{{end}}{{if .Has "pgx"}}
## Database

This project uses [pgx](https://github.com/jackc/pgx) for PostgreSQL. Set
`DATABASE_URL` (for example `postgres://user:pass@localhost:5432/db`) before
starting the server.
{{end}}{{if .Has "sqlc"}}
## Generating database code

Write your schema in `db/schema.sql` and your queries in `db/query.sql`, then
run:

```sh
make sqlc
```

This generates type-safe Go code with [sqlc](https://sqlc.dev).
{{end}}